                    "company": "Movies that Matter",
                    "description": "The Dutch organisation Movies that Matter offers revealing films and documentaries about human rights and a fair and sustainable world. Movies that Matter shows these films including debates and interview sessions during the yearly Movies that Matter Festival in The Hague, in diverse Dutch film theatres, at schools, during events and supports human rights film screenings in non-western countries.\n\nProjects \u201cEvents & Advice\u201d:\n-Movies that Matter On Tour: organisation of film program in fifteen Dutch cities. \n-Events: Developing and organizing film screenings and debates in cooperation with several partner organizations (such as Plan Nederland, UNHCR, IDFA en NIOD).\n-Movies that Matter Label & A La Carte: facilitating film screenings for a broad audience while making use of the Movies that Matter film database.\n-Advice: giving advice concerning the organisation of events and human rights films and documentaries. \n\nResponsibilities: Implementation of running projects, concept development: developing new ideas into projects, fundraising and acquisition, financial administration, developing debates: research, inviting guest speakers, hosts, content development and unfolding questions, production during events and monitoring and evaluation of project activities.\n\nWebsite: www.moviesthatmatter.nl",
