                    "company": "lokaalmondiaal",
                    "description": "From January 2013 until August 2014 I coordinated all Lokaalmondiaal programs concerning International Journalism. The largest program is called Beyond Your World.\n\nBeyond Your World (BYW) is an international journalism exchange program. Lokaalmondiaal has implemented this program since 2006 but in 2013 and 2014 we expanded the program to five other EU countries.\n\nDuring this two-year program, a total amount of approximately 10,000 students from 6 EU countries enrolled (partly or fully) in the training program about global reporting which was offered by universities and media schools in their own countries. A total amount of 440 students from the Netherlands, Belgium, England, Germany, Portugal and Bulgaria went on overseas placements to developing countries in order to make a total amount of 1760 journalism productions (film, radio, photography, written, multimedia). \n\nTaking into account the interconnectedness among countries worldwide, we highly value the role of international journalism. Therefore, the overall objective of the program is to inspire and enable the next generation of EU journalists and media professionals to inform the European audience about development issues and other foreign topics, thereby generating greater critical understanding among EU (and global) citizens.",
